Introduction

GWSN (Korean: 공원소녀; Japanese: 公園少女; also known as Girls in the Park) was a seven-member multinational independent girl group. They debuted on September 5, 2018 with the mini-album The Park In The Night Part One.

The group was set to hold numerous events to increase their popularity pre-debut until the final group debut.

On June 14, the subsidiary of Kiwi Media Group, Kiwi Pop (now closed), announced their first girl group with a teaser image and the opening of their social media. On the same day, their debut date was set to June 18. Following this, from June 19 to 23, the seven members were revealed as Minju, Lena, Anne, Soso, Seoryoung, Miya and Seokyoung respectively.

On January 22, 2023, it was revealed that GWSN had won the first trial of their lawsuits against The Wave Music for terminating their exclusive contracts, stating that they've been neglected since 2021 and are unable to continue their entertainment activities this way. In addition, members were forced to leave their dorms since February 2022 because the company stopped paying rent, providing any practice space, didn't provide paperwork for foreign members' VISAs resulting in them having to pay fines and more, without any answers by the company for 30 days.

In June 2023, Miya announced that around the time they filed to terminate their contract in January, they disbanded.
